{
  "stem": "18102.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But in preparation for that, my father also painted black all the windows because of the need for blackout, which the government requested that everyone do.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So things were quite different once we, once we moved.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I heard the bombings, and I heard the gunfire.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, the fright came not from inside but from as a reaction to the fright that I saw in my mother's face and my father's.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I myself didn't know, I don't think, the fright involved.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a transmitted fright and, indeed, that transmitted itself very well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I became frightened as a consequence of that transmittal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't know what to be frightened of until when I was older.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I knew that it was good enough for me that my parents were frightened.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That frightened me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[BACKROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, [SIGHS] [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was all very strange and very, I guess the word is frightening, because the, the tension was 24 hours.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The schools were let out so that suddenly my parents were there all the time, at least in the first few days of the war.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Pretty soon my father left altogether before the Germans, in fact, invaded Bialystok or entered Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was already gone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in the first few days we were all together.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When-- the, the memory that I have is of one air raid where we would all huddle in the, in the vestibule of the building.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father didn't-- there was a basement, but he was afraid to put us in the basement in case the-- if building was hit we wouldn't be able to get out of the basement.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
